#Text=Parajet Skycar expedition takes off from London to Timbuktu
#Text=Tuesday , January 20 , 2009
#Text=The Waterman Aerobile #6 , seen here in the Steven F. Udvar-Hazy Center , was an earlier attempt at a flying car .
#Text=Two explorers have set off from Knightsbridge , London Wednesday morning ( 0900 GMT ) in a propeller-powered dune buggy heading for the Sahara .

#Text=Giles Cardozo , age 29 , from Dorset , with chief pilot and expedition leader Neil Laughton , age 45 , an ex-SAS officer , will fly and drive the amazing two-seater vehicle more than 6,000-km ( 3,750-miles ) to fabled Timbuktu on February 20 .
#Text=" I just ca n't wait to see their faces when we fly in and start playing football with them .

column1: #Text=The Skycar will thereafter fly over the high-altitude Pyrenees near Andorra , and would cross over the 14-km ( nine-mile ) Strait of Gibraltar .
#Text=The prepared journey also includes the route through Mauritania , Atlas Mountains in Morocco and into Mali .
#Text=It will further cross the harsh environment of Sahara ’s remote “ Rub ' al Khali " ( empty quarter ) , for up to two weeks amid real fears of terrorist attacks .

#Text=" We 're going to have to cope with wind chill temperatures as low as -30 deg C and blistering heat of up to 50 deg C. But it 's been fully tested at a secret location and it 100 per cent works , " he added .
#Text=The Parajet Skycar is a prototype flying car .
#Text=It was developed by British paramotor manufacturer Parajet .
#Text=The flying car utilizes a paramotor and a parafoil attached to a modified dune buggy to achieve sustained level flight .
#Text=Should the engine fail , the vehicle can glide back to the ground .
#Text=Should the canopy rip , an emergency reserve parachute would be deployed .
#Text=It requires three minutes to convert it from a car to an aircraft .
#Text=The prototype runs on biodiesel and is fully road-legal .
#Text=In 2004
#Text=British engineer Giles Cardozo , a paramotor manufacturer , has invented a fan-powered flying car to prove the Skycar is real and works .
#Text=“ I started making a paramotor on wheels that you sit on and take off and it suddenly occurred to me , ‘ Why not just have a car that does everything ? ’ ” Cardozo said .
#Text=His Wiltshire -based company Parajet built the paramotor that the adventurer Bear Grylls did fly near Everest in 2008 .
#Text=In 1998 , Grylls , aged 23 , became the youngest British to ascend Mount Everest .
#Text=In May 2007 , Grylls and Cardozo departed from Pheriche , about 32 kilometres south of Mount Everest .

#Text=Cardozo has claimed he may finally have made it .
#Text=“ I ’ve been dreaming about making flying cars since I was a boy , thinking about all the ways it could be done and seeing how all the other people in the world have done it wrong .
#Text=No one ’s ever made one that really does work that you can go out and buy .
#Text=But here ’s the ultimate solution : it ’s cheap , it ’s safe , it works , all the technology ’s already there .
#Text=So I pushed ahead and thought , ‘ We ’ve got to do it ’ , ” he said .

#Text=If the Skycar becomes successful , Cardozo ’s company plans a limited production with a selling price of £35,000 to £40,000 for a standard model and £60,000 for a high-performance sports version .
#Text=“ It will be a serious aircraft but also a proper road machine , with acceleration to match your average sports car , ” says Cardozo .
#Text=“ I ’m not going to sell millions of them but even if we sell 20 we ’ll be laughing , ” he added .

#Text=The explorers , with the aid of sponsors , supporters and benefactor Sir Ranulph Twisleton-Wykeham-Fiennes , 3rd Baronet OBE ( known as ' Ranulph ( Ran ) Fiennes ' ) , have aimed to raise more than £100,000 for some charities including an African orphanage .
